Citation.sTitle: Isobaric Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium Data for Binary Systems of Anisole with Methyl Acetate, Ethyl Acetate, n-Propyl Acetate, and Isopropyl Acetate at 93.9 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Present work reports experimental isobaric vapor-liquid equilibrium data at 93.9 kPa pressure using a dynamic recirculation still for four binary pairs of acetates with anisole. Suitability of the experimental data for modelling was established by performing Herington area test, Van Ness test and mean absolute deviation test. Binary interaction parameters necessary for process modelling were derived through regression of the VLE data for Wilson, NRTL, and UNIQUAC activity coefficient models with a suitable objective function. VLE data in the form of T-x,y plots indicates no formation of azeotrope for all pairs.
Citation.sKeyword: Isopropyl acetate. INTRODUCTION In perfume industries anisole is widely used as a flavouring agent because of its aromatic odour.
